{"id":"towers","term":"Towers","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Of Babel (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 11:4\">Gen. 11:4</a>), Edar (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 35:21\">Gen. 35:21</a>), Penuel (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Judges 8:9\">Judg. 8:9</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Judges 8:17\">17</a>), Shechem (9:46), David (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Song of Solomon 4:4\">Cant. 4:4</a>), Lebanon (7:4), Syene (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezekiel 29:10\">Ezek. 29:10</a>), Hananeel (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Zechariah 14:10\">Zech. 14:10</a>), Siloam (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 13:4\">Luke 13:4</a>). There were several towers in Jerusalem (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Chronicles 26:9\">2 Chr. 26:9</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 48:12\">Ps. 48:12</a>). They were erected for various purposes, as watch-towers in vineyard (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 5:2\">Isa. 5:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 21:33\">Matt. 21:33</a>) and towers for defence.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 11:4","Genesis 35:21","Judges 8:9","Judges 8:17","Song of Solomon 4:4","Ezekiel 29:10","Zechariah 14:10","Luke 13:4","2 Chronicles 26:9","Psalms 48:12","Isaiah 5:2","Matthew 21:33"]}